_source.productName: Brendale - Collectormania Antique, Collectable & Record Fair
_source.productDescription:
Join in at the Brendale Antique, Collectable & Record fair.

They are back on Brisbanes Northside for our not to be missed, two day event.

This long running event held at the Southpine Sports Centre features over 60 dealers and an eclectic mix of treasures you won't find anywhere else! Japanese and Chinese antiques, jade items, ancient Roman coins, pottery, records, man cave pieces, military collectables, art deco and retro pieces, antique jewellery, gold, silver, coins, stamps, vintage toys, homewares, english porcelain, coloured glassware, uranium and opalescent glass, vintage kitchenalia, dolls, haberdashery and linen, vintage fashion and accessories, and so much more. Whether you're a seasoned collector, a vintage lover, or simply on the hunt for something unique, there's something here for everyone! Don't miss out on your chance to experience the charm of history through their 60 plus  specialist displays, all under one roof.

There is a lovely onsite cafe and there will be an ATM available for your convenience. Also go into the draw to win AUD100 VISA gift card with their lucky door prize!

_source.productName: Hungerford Horse and Motorbike Gymkhana
_source.productDescription:
This incredible Outback Sporting Event is perfect for Horse & Motorbike lovers. Join in on the action or watch this fun-filled, family orientated event for all ages!

The Hungerford Sports Association holds its annual Horse & Motorbike Gymkhana on the October long weekend providing a great Outback Sporting Event for both Horse and Motorbike lovers. This weekend is a fun filled, family orientated event for people of all ages!

It kicks off Friday night at the Royal Mail Hotel with a camp oven meal and live entertainment! Saturday is jam packed full of horse and motorbike events for both children and adults, as well as novelty events such as the famous Mulga Mac's bicycle race, a tug of war and sprint races for men, women and children. The day winds up with a live band and licensed bar in the evening as well as an incredible auction where the funds raised benefit the Royal Flying Doctor Service and other local charities.

So come along and enjoy a fabulous, fun-filled, family weekend!

_source.productDescription:
Guys and Gals, it's time to turn up the heat and roll out the giggles at their "Sizzling Chilli, Beer and Sausage Fest for Charity"  full of the wurst puns and hotdoggin' fun!

Spice It Up! Feeling daring? Their chilli sauce stalls are hotter than a jalapeno in a sauna! Free samples galore, so bring a big shopping trolley and stock up for summer barbecue season!

Chilli-eating comps, and the Men's Wet T-Shirt comp  Can you handle the heat in the chilli challenge? Will your sausage-tossing skills impress the crowd?  Then get ready to get wet dudes! 

Making a Hot Dog Difference: Sure, they're all about silly puns and belly laughs, but our real mission is to make a difference! Your AUD2 entry, every sausage bite and chilli sample contributes to local charities. They're "linking" arms to make the world a better place, one sausage at a time! Supporting Prostate Cancer Research and Rural Aid.

Come one, come all to The Sizzling Chilli, Beer & Sausage Fest for Charity: where hotdogs find their buns, chilli sauce gets the spotlight, and laughter is the special sauce that makes it all worth it!

The workshop will run for two hours and is suitable for beginners through to advanced potters.

_source.productDescription:
Prepare to get off the beaten track, off-road and on uneven ground. This course is guaranteed to get you panting with an uphill challenge for everyone. 

Course: 6km, 14km and 24km

Start/Finish: Cnr Pinnacle Septimus & Pinnacle Station Roads

The uphill event kicks off with a thrilling challenge for all participants. Prepare to hit the ground running as you face a demanding climb at the start.

For those opting for the long course, get ready to venture into the picturesque Mia Mia State Forest, where history meets nature. As you navigate through the trail, you'll pass by a fascinating historic homestead, adding a touch of heritage to your experience.

This trail features a mix of technical sections, including an initial steep climb and a thrilling fast descent. Along the way, you'll encounter enjoyable creek crossings and varied terrain to test your navigation skills and keep the adventure alive.

Mia Mia (Captain's Crossing) is conveniently located a mere 6km away from the iconic Pinnacle Family Hotel, offering a sense of proximity and accessibility.  Situated just 45 minutes from Mackay and a short drive to Eungella, it's an ideal location to get off the beaten track.
